               <p>SECOND COUNT, stating it to be fixed to a building of his.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210411-208-person1985">
                  THOMAS 
                  SEPTIMUS JONES
               <interp inst="t18210411-208-person1985" type="surname" value="SEPTIMUS JONES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210411-208-person1985" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210411-208-person1985" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the owner of a house in <placeName id="t18210411-208-crimeloc1275">Curtain-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18210411-208-crimeloc1275" type="placeName" value="Curtain-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18210411-208-crimeloc1275" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210411-208-off1273 t18210411-208-crimeloc1275"></join>. I saw it about a fortnight previous to the robbery, the lead-work was complete then. The house was untenanted. On the 6th of April I received information; went and found all the water pipe cut from the back kitchen.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210411-208-person1986">
                  JOSEPH 
                  READY
               <interp inst="t18210411-208-person1986" type="surname" value="READY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210411-208-person1986" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210411-208-person1986" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a hat-maker, and work next door to the house. On the 3d of April, about half past nine at night, I was alarmed by a noise in the next house; I gave the alarm to the person who had the letting of the house. I went into the house, and opened the door myself with the key, and in the top room I found the prisoner alone; I gave him to the watchman. After he was put in the watch-house, I went down into the kitchen, and found the lead laying on the floor; it was torn from the wall; there was about nine feet of pipe, fresh torn, and cut in different pieces.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210411-208-person1987">
                  WILLIAM 
                  MORETON
               <interp inst="t18210411-208-person1987" type="surname" value="MORETON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210411-208-person1987" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210411-208-person1987" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner was brought to the watch-house; next morning I went to the kitchen and found the pipe torn off the wall; it weighed 24 lbs. I found him in great distress.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The prisoner pleaded distress.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18210411-208-verdict1276" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18210411-208-verdict1276" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 24.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18210411-208-punish1277" type="punishmentDescription">
